-When we first arrived,
I got off the airplane,

00:50:51.880 --> 00:50:57.340 align:middle line:84%
and it was like
a whoosh of heat.

00:50:57.340 --> 00:51:00.700 align:middle line:84%
-I felt weird because I had
to go in the immigrant line.

00:51:00.700 --> 00:51:02.430 align:middle line:90%
Now the table's turned.

00:51:02.430 --> 00:51:05.140 align:middle line:84%
-As always, when you come
out of the plan in Accra,

00:51:05.140 --> 00:51:08.915 align:middle line:84%
at the airport, you're hit
with the humidity and the heat.

00:51:08.915 --> 00:51:10.856 align:middle line:84%
It's like, oh, yeah,
we're in Africa.

00:51:10.856 --> 00:51:17.200 align:middle line:90%


00:51:17.200 --> 00:51:18.680 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:51:18.680 --> 00:51:21.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So that was just
the beginning, we saw,

00:51:21.200 --> 00:51:22.160 align:middle line:90%
of your journey.

00:51:22.160 --> 00:51:24.345 align:middle line:90%
And so how often do you do this?

00:51:24.345 --> 00:51:25.470 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Every other year.

00:51:25.470 --> 00:51:26.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Every other year?

00:51:26.240 --> 00:51:26.865 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Yeah.

00:51:26.865 --> 00:51:28.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And how do you
choose who to bring?

00:51:28.660 --> 00:51:30.284 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAHAM: It's actually
self-selecting,

00:51:30.284 --> 00:51:34.340 align:middle line:84%
because they have to
have been of service.

00:51:34.340 --> 00:51:36.970 align:middle line:84%
Twice a month, as part
of the mentoring program,

00:51:36.970 --> 00:51:38.390 align:middle line:90%
we go and volunteer.

00:51:38.390 --> 00:51:40.890 align:middle line:84%
So we look to see which
young people had been doing

00:51:40.890 --> 00:51:43.610 align:middle line:84%
a volunteering work,
which one of them

00:51:43.610 --> 00:51:47.110 align:middle line:84%
have been coming to meetings,
and where they're at,

00:51:47.110 --> 00:51:49.010 align:middle line:90%
to see if they're mature enough.

00:51:49.010 --> 00:51:51.030 align:middle line:84%
Because what I tell
them is, you're

00:51:51.030 --> 00:51:52.449 align:middle line:84%
ambassadors for
the United States

00:51:52.449 --> 00:51:53.740 align:middle line:90%
when you go out of the country.

00:51:53.740 --> 00:51:55.610 align:middle line:84%
You are representing
not only yourself,

00:51:55.610 --> 00:51:57.151 align:middle line:84%
but you're representing
your country.

00:51:57.151 --> 00:51:58.655 align:middle line:90%
So you've got to represent.

00:51:58.655 --> 00:52:00.680 align:middle line:84%
So it's like, are
you ready for that?

00:52:00.680 --> 00:52:02.120 align:middle line:84%
Are you ready to
be an ambassador

00:52:02.120 --> 00:52:03.450 align:middle line:90%
for your own country?

00:52:03.450 --> 00:52:05.200 align:middle line:84%
And when you frame
it that way, it's

00:52:05.200 --> 00:52:06.800 align:middle line:90%
really very self-selecting.

00:52:06.800 --> 00:52:11.110 align:middle line:84%
And we watch to see-- me and
my other artist facilitators,

00:52:11.110 --> 00:52:14.777 align:middle line:84%
we look to see which ones
are always giving excuses.

00:52:14.777 --> 00:52:16.860 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't come to the
meeting because [MUMBLING].

00:52:16.860 --> 00:52:17.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:52:17.470 --> 00:52:20.094 align:middle line:84%
So they have to have
pre-qualifications and stick

00:52:20.094 --> 00:52:21.510 align:middle line:84%
with it for a long
period of time?

00:52:21.510 --> 00:52:21.634 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Yes.

00:52:21.634 --> 00:52:22.640 align:middle line:90%
For a period of time.

00:52:22.640 --> 00:52:23.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that's
self-selecting.

00:52:23.490 --> 00:52:24.340 align:middle line:90%
That's interesting.

00:52:24.340 --> 00:52:25.180 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Very much so.

00:52:25.180 --> 00:52:27.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How do you keep up
your spiritual practice?

00:52:27.320 --> 00:52:28.987 align:middle line:90%
You do so much for others.

00:52:28.987 --> 00:52:30.820 align:middle line:84%
And I see that it gives
back to you so much.

00:52:30.820 --> 00:52:31.611 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Oh, yeah.

00:52:31.611 --> 00:52:32.490 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yeah.

00:52:32.490 --> 00:52:34.326 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But what
is your practice?

00:52:34.326 --> 00:52:35.200 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: I meditate.

00:52:35.200 --> 00:52:38.680 align:middle line:84%
I make sure that I feed
myself with great food,

00:52:38.680 --> 00:52:41.902 align:middle line:84%
like listening to "The
Aware Show" with Lisa Garr.

00:52:41.902 --> 00:52:43.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You learn a lot, yes.

00:52:43.110 --> 00:52:44.007 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Yes.

00:52:44.007 --> 00:52:45.340 align:middle line:90%
And I'm very serious about that.

00:52:45.340 --> 00:52:46.950 align:middle line:84%
I mean, your show--
it's OK, it's

00:52:46.950 --> 00:52:50.110 align:middle line:90%
Wednesday and Thursday, 1:00.

00:52:50.110 --> 00:52:52.460 align:middle line:84%
Of course, Doctor
Beckwith-- Reverend Michael

00:52:52.460 --> 00:52:54.740 align:middle line:84%
is one of my mentors
and teachers.

00:52:54.740 --> 00:52:55.800 align:middle line:90%
So I go to Agappe.

00:52:55.800 --> 00:52:58.680 align:middle line:84%
And I try to do what
I teach the children

00:52:58.680 --> 00:53:03.780 align:middle line:84%
and make sure I get massages
and eat well and hike and do

00:53:03.780 --> 00:53:06.300 align:middle line:84%
all things that I enjoy
that I give to them.

00:53:06.300 --> 00:53:08.907 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you ever get
depressed or challenged?

00:53:08.907 --> 00:53:09.990 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Challenged, yes.

00:53:09.990 --> 00:53:11.889 align:middle line:84%
I don't think I
really get depressed.

00:53:11.889 --> 00:53:13.222 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I don't think so either.

00:53:13.222 --> 00:53:15.110 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:53:15.110 --> 00:53:17.050 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAHAM: But
challenged, oh, yes.

00:53:17.050 --> 00:53:20.180 align:middle line:84%
And frustrated sometimes,
if it's like, oh,

00:53:20.180 --> 00:53:23.070 align:middle line:84%
this isn't working out the way
I think it should or whatever.

00:53:23.070 --> 00:53:25.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because most people
would use the excuse of,

00:53:25.890 --> 00:53:28.880 align:middle line:84%
the system-- the system-- I
can't penetrate the system.

00:53:28.880 --> 00:53:29.610 align:middle line:90%
You have.

00:53:29.610 --> 00:53:30.426 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Oh, yeah.

00:53:30.426 --> 00:53:32.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you ever get
frustrated or blocks there?

00:53:32.550 --> 00:53:33.360 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Oh, sure.

00:53:33.360 --> 00:53:37.680 align:middle line:84%
I mean, because not everyone
is gung ho about this program.

00:53:37.680 --> 00:53:41.050 align:middle line:84%
Although I will say--
I will say that I've

00:53:41.050 --> 00:53:42.740 align:middle line:90%
been doing this for a long time.

00:53:42.740 --> 00:53:44.570 align:middle line:84%
And probation
officers and teachers

00:53:44.570 --> 00:53:47.090 align:middle line:84%
will tell you they're used
to all kinds of people coming

00:53:47.090 --> 00:53:49.930 align:middle line:84%
in promising the
world or whatever.

00:53:49.930 --> 00:53:52.619 align:middle line:84%
And at least they
know I'm consistent.

00:53:52.619 --> 00:53:54.160 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You have a
good track record.

00:53:54.160 --> 00:53:54.390 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Yeah.

00:53:54.390 --> 00:53:54.931 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:53:54.931 --> 00:53:58.470 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAHAM: And it speaks for
itself because at these sites,

00:53:58.470 --> 00:54:01.410 align:middle line:84%
administration changes
every two years or so.

00:54:01.410 --> 00:54:04.660 align:middle line:84%
So it's not like there's
one particular principal who

00:54:04.660 --> 00:54:08.015 align:middle line:84%
just loves me personally
and keeps bringing me in.

00:54:08.015 --> 00:54:09.390 align:middle line:84%
Every two or three
years, there's

00:54:09.390 --> 00:54:12.200 align:middle line:84%
a different administration--
different teachers

00:54:12.200 --> 00:54:14.320 align:middle line:90%
that I have to be vetted by.

00:54:14.320 --> 00:54:16.299 align:middle line:84%
But you know what keeps
us in the facilities?

00:54:16.299 --> 00:54:16.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What?

00:54:16.840 --> 00:54:17.798 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: The children.

00:54:17.798 --> 00:54:20.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, they say how
much they-- and they change

00:54:20.590 --> 00:54:21.580 align:middle line:90%
and they respond.

00:54:21.580 --> 00:54:22.280 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Yeah.

00:54:22.280 --> 00:54:24.110 align:middle line:90%
It's the children.

00:54:24.110 --> 00:54:28.360 align:middle line:84%
We've had students that have
done-- they write letters.

00:54:28.360 --> 00:54:30.490 align:middle line:84%
They've written to the
Department of Justice.

00:54:30.490 --> 00:54:33.220 align:middle line:84%
They write letters to probation
officer saying, please

00:54:33.220 --> 00:54:35.820 align:middle line:90%
bring this program back.

00:54:35.820 --> 00:54:38.070 align:middle line:84%
I bring students that have
been through our program

00:54:38.070 --> 00:54:41.880 align:middle line:84%
back to the facilities to
meet the other children.

00:54:41.880 --> 00:54:45.180 align:middle line:84%
One of them is one of my
assistants, Quiyona Bridges,

00:54:45.180 --> 00:54:47.260 align:middle line:84%
who-- at some point, I'm
sure you'll meet her,

00:54:47.260 --> 00:54:49.800 align:middle line:90%
Lisa-- beautiful young woman.

00:54:49.800 --> 00:54:51.010 align:middle line:90%
I met her when she was 14.

00:54:51.010 --> 00:54:53.349 align:middle line:84%
She now works for the
Spirit Waking Foundation.

00:54:53.349 --> 00:54:54.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my God.

00:54:54.140 --> 00:54:56.320 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAHAM: Some of them
work with us so they can--

00:54:56.320 --> 00:54:57.945 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: To have her
go back in and talk

00:54:57.945 --> 00:55:00.547 align:middle line:84%
with those children has
got to be so powerful.

00:55:00.547 --> 00:55:02.380 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAHAM: Very powerful,
because now they're

00:55:02.380 --> 00:55:04.200 align:middle line:90%
not just hearing it from me.

00:55:04.200 --> 00:55:07.030 align:middle line:84%
And she can say, look,
I went from point A

00:55:07.030 --> 00:55:09.700 align:middle line:84%
to point B. I was once
where you're sitting,

00:55:09.700 --> 00:55:11.340 align:middle line:90%
right there, with my attitude.

00:55:11.340 --> 00:55:14.300 align:middle line:90%
I was an angry child.

00:55:14.300 --> 00:55:17.180 align:middle line:84%
And it's true, because if anyone
had told me that this young--

00:55:17.180 --> 00:55:21.010 align:middle line:84%
she's now this elegant
young woman with dignity.

00:55:21.010 --> 00:55:23.430 align:middle line:84%
And if they'd told me that
she would be working with me,

00:55:23.430 --> 00:55:25.400 align:middle line:90%
I would have said, oh, no.

00:55:25.400 --> 00:55:26.737 align:middle line:90%
With that attitude?

00:55:26.737 --> 00:55:28.570 align:middle line:84%
Back then, I would've
been like, no, no, no.

00:55:28.570 --> 00:55:29.740 align:middle line:90%
I don't think so.

00:55:29.740 --> 00:55:33.030 align:middle line:84%
But here she is, a
beautiful young woman

00:55:33.030 --> 00:55:34.530 align:middle line:90%
that teaches me all the time.

00:55:34.530 --> 00:55:36.070 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It doesn't
necessarily even

00:55:36.070 --> 00:55:38.514 align:middle line:84%
have to be, oh, I had
this vision as a child

00:55:38.514 --> 00:55:39.930 align:middle line:84%
that I was going
to be doing this.

00:55:39.930 --> 00:55:42.140 align:middle line:84%
She came from a totally
different set of circumstances.

00:55:42.140 --> 00:55:42.820 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: That's right.

00:55:42.820 --> 00:55:43.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And you can change.

00:55:43.720 --> 00:55:44.410 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: That's right.

00:55:44.410 --> 00:55:44.740 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:55:44.740 --> 00:55:45.410 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that's
a huge message.

00:55:45.410 --> 00:55:46.240 align:middle line:90%
How old is she now?

00:55:46.240 --> 00:55:47.200 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: She's 22.

00:55:47.200 --> 00:55:47.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:55:47.880 --> 00:55:48.505 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Yeah.

00:55:48.505 --> 00:55:49.490 align:middle line:90%
22.

00:55:49.490 --> 00:55:52.240 align:middle line:84%
And she has a daughter--
beautiful child.

00:55:52.240 --> 00:55:55.930 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, we call her the
little Spirit Awakening.

00:55:55.930 --> 00:55:58.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So what
is up for you now?

00:55:58.240 --> 00:55:59.930 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you've done
so much and you're

00:55:59.930 --> 00:56:01.860 align:middle line:90%
going so many different places.

00:56:01.860 --> 00:56:03.680 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: I know.

00:56:03.680 --> 00:56:06.880 align:middle line:84%
Actually, celebrating
our 20th year,

00:56:06.880 --> 00:56:09.320 align:middle line:84%
we have sort of some
major milestones

00:56:09.320 --> 00:56:11.760 align:middle line:84%
we want to hit--
the Spirit House,

00:56:11.760 --> 00:56:14.780 align:middle line:84%
really making sure that the
mentoring program is online,

00:56:14.780 --> 00:56:17.737 align:middle line:84%
and then making the film out of
the play-- "Spirit Awakening."

00:56:17.737 --> 00:56:19.320 align:middle line:84%
I've written the
screenplay and it's--

00:56:19.320 --> 00:56:20.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, great.

00:56:20.090 --> 00:56:20.715 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Yeah.

00:56:20.715 --> 00:56:23.260 align:middle line:84%
And one of my other
mentors in the business

00:56:23.260 --> 00:56:27.070 align:middle line:84%
is the producer Robert
Chartoff, who is a love.

00:56:27.070 --> 00:56:28.490 align:middle line:90%
He did all the Rocky movies.

00:56:28.490 --> 00:56:29.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:56:29.030 --> 00:56:30.446 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAHAM: And so
he's mentoring me

00:56:30.446 --> 00:56:33.070 align:middle line:84%
in terms of bringing this
story to the big screen.

00:56:33.070 --> 00:56:33.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Beautiful.

00:56:33.820 --> 00:56:35.880 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAHAM: So those
are the main things.

00:56:35.880 --> 00:56:37.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Can't wait to see it.

00:56:37.660 --> 00:56:38.530 align:middle line:90%
Sounds exciting.

00:56:38.530 --> 00:56:39.780 align:middle line:90%
You're up to so many things.

00:56:39.780 --> 00:56:42.880 align:middle line:84%
You've taught us so much and
just explaining your life

00:56:42.880 --> 00:56:46.620 align:middle line:84%
about overcoming adversity,
about meeting new challenges,

00:56:46.620 --> 00:56:50.890 align:middle line:84%
about taking action, about truly
authentically being who you are

00:56:50.890 --> 00:56:53.260 align:middle line:84%
and healing herself
through helping others.

00:56:53.260 --> 00:56:54.210 align:middle line:90%
Just amazing.

00:56:54.210 --> 00:56:56.490 align:middle line:84%
And thank you so
much for being here.

00:56:56.490 --> 00:56:58.320 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAHAM: Lisa,
thank you very much.

00:56:58.320 --> 00:57:00.220 align:middle line:90%
What an honor and a privilege.

00:57:00.220 --> 00:57:01.720 align:middle line:90%
And again, I love you, Lisa.

00:57:01.720 --> 00:57:02.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Aw, you're kidding.

00:57:02.280 --> 00:57:03.240 align:middle line:90%
The honor is mine.

00:57:03.240 --> 00:57:03.680 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAHAM: Thank you so much.

